hopobject.body: There's a three month trial period culchethhealth.co.uk A student's EFC is calculated by the federal government using information collected via the Free Application for Federal Student Aid. It takes into consideration income, assets, benefits and family size to calculate what students and their parents can reasonably pay toward a year of college. The figure can vary from school to school, as some institutions use their own formula to calculate family contribution.
